
// Reference: https://www.journaldev.com/16635/collections-class-java-util-collections

Collections is a class in java to work with Collections. (Ya ya we have Collection interface too)
methods operating on or returning Collections.

Supports polymorphic algorithms (i.e achieve same functionality using diff data structures)

It has all the Static methods in it. (Thats why we call them using ``Collections.sort()`` )

Methods include:											note: ~ means optional argument

			sort(List l, ~Comparator c)             // Sorts the List according to provided custom comparator or 
														natural comparsion if not provided
		
				// Collections.sort(li);
				// Collections.sort(li, Comparator.reverseOrder())
				
T			max(Colleciton c, ~Comparator c)        // Returns max element in collection
			
T			min(Collection c, ~Comparator c)       	// Returns min element in collection
		
int			binarySearch(Collections <E extends comparator> , k key)     // returns index of the specified element in the list
		
boolean		addAll(Collection c, elements,,,)  		// adds all the elements in the list
		
int			frequency(Collection c, element)     	// Returns frequency of the element in the specified list

void        swap(list, i , j)             			// Swapping ith element with jth element
		
			copy(Collection dest, Collection src)	// copies the elements of 
		
			fill(Collection c, element)            	// Replaces all the elements of Collection with
											   		// specified elements
											   
int			indexOfSubList(List fullList, List sublist)   // Returns the index of the occurence of sublist in the fulllist
				// lastIndexOfSublist() also		
									   		
Queue		asLifoQueue(Dequeue d)